@DATABASE "Turrican"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - T - Turrican"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - T
                   ====================================

                                 Turrican
                                 ========



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Continues" rxs "address command zxampoke(28670,0)"}      28670,0
@{"Continues = x     " rxs "address command zxampoke(28103,255)"}      28103,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Gyros = x         " rxs "address command zxampoke(28207,20) zxampoke(36199,20)"}      28207,x:36199,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Infinite Gyros    " rxs "address command zxampoke(31501,0)"}      31501,0
@{"Infinite Lives    " rxs "address command zxampoke(28581,183"}      28581,183
@{"Lives = x         " rxs "address command zxampoke(28675,255) zxampoke(36256,255)"}      28675,x:36256,x (x= 1-255)


                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         Note although the "Gyros = x" POKE can go
                         up to 255, if you have any more than 20, it
                         gets very messy.


                         This is one of my POKEs. Enjoy!

                         Rastan.
@endnode
